00:56:01.959 --> 00:56:06.040
videos up on YouTube because I give it at so many different workshops.

00:56:06.040 --> 00:56:09.879
You can look for that content or you can come join us live in the workshop.

00:56:09.879 --> 00:56:11.080
It's always more fun in person.

00:56:13.239 --> 00:56:14.600
And you're also giving a talk.

00:56:15.560 --> 00:56:17.639
And I will also be giving a talk.

00:56:18.520 --> 00:56:21.879
My talk is called Context is King.

00:56:21.879 --> 00:56:24.760
I'll be in the Making Great Tables session.

00:56:25.560 --> 00:56:33.399
And we're going to be talking about variable labels in R, which I think is a not very well

00:56:33.399 --> 00:56:34.360
known feature.

00:56:34.360 --> 00:56:38.679
And I think there's a lot of advantages to using this feature that I'm going to talk

00:56:38.679 --> 00:56:39.179
about.

00:56:41.159 --> 00:56:45.560
How do you prepare for everything that's going to be at the same time?

00:56:46.520 --> 00:56:51.399
Well, luckily for PositConf, I have well-tested teaching material.

00:56:52.439 --> 00:56:56.199
I didn't actually try to give a talk the first year I was teaching a workshop.

00:56:56.199 --> 00:56:57.080
That would have been crazy.

00:56:57.080 --> 00:56:59.479
I know people that do that, but that's not for me.

00:56:59.479 --> 00:57:01.560
So at least the workshop's pretty well set.

00:57:03.080 --> 00:57:03.479
Awesome.

00:57:03.479 --> 00:57:05.639
Well, I'm so excited to see you there.

00:57:06.280 --> 00:57:11.239
I did just want to let everybody know that, so you've probably heard, when people get

00:57:11.239 --> 00:57:17.000
accepted for talks at PositConf, we have them go through speaker training, if they

00:57:17.000 --> 00:57:19.800
want, with this organization called Articulation.

00:57:20.600 --> 00:57:26.679
And Articulation is going to actually join the Data Science Hangout next week.

00:57:26.679 --> 00:57:33.000
So if you want to learn from them without yet being a PositConf speaker, I encourage

00:57:33.000 --> 00:57:35.639
you to join next week's Data Science Hangout too.

00:57:36.439 --> 00:57:39.479
Blythe and Acacia from Articulation will be here.

00:57:40.199 --> 00:57:41.080
That'd be cool.

00:57:41.080 --> 00:57:41.580
Yeah.

00:57:42.520 --> 00:57:42.919
Awesome.

00:57:42.919 --> 00:57:44.840
Well, thank you so much, Shannon.

00:57:44.840 --> 00:57:49.719
I really appreciate you taking the time to join us and sharing your experience.

00:57:49.719 --> 00:57:55.560
And thank you to everybody here in the chat with all these amazing links and everything

00:57:55.560 --> 00:57:56.520
that was shared here too.

00:57:57.719 --> 00:57:58.360
Thank you all.

